Package org.trikkle.annotations

Class HalfLink

java.lang.Object
org.trikkle.annotations.HalfLink
public final class HalfLink extends Object
A link that has not yet been connected to its dependencies. Dependencies may be inferred through the method toFullLinks(List), where HalfLinks are converted into full links by using each other as context.
Since:
0.1.0

  • Method Details

    • toFullLinks

      public static List<Link> toFullLinks(List<HalfLink> halfLinks)
      Converts a list of half links into a list of full links by using one another as context. For every HalfLink, all starting datums (i.e ., those that are not returned by any other half links in the list) will be combined into a single starting DiscreteNode. Any half link that already has dependencies manually set will be added to the list as is.
      Parameters:
      halfLinks - the half links to convert
      Returns:
      a list of full links
      See Also:
      • Link
      • DiscreteNode
